l1sign
------------------------------------------
l1sign is a portable implementation of the Lamport-Diffie one-time signature
scheme (LD-OTS). It allows users to generate key pairs, sign messages, and
verify signatures.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.6-1
  libgcrypt20-1.8.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-9.3.0-2
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://janikrabe.com/projects/l1sign/

Canonical download:
  https://code.janikrabe.com/l1sign/snapshot/l1sign-0.2.0.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack l1sign-0.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./l1sign-0.2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/l1sign-0.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/l1sign-0.2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(l1sign)
  /usr/bin/l1sign.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/l1sign.README
  /usr/share/doc/l1sign/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/l1sign/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/l1sign/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/l1sign.1.gz

